reference "tab:hod"

\end_inset

.
 The smoothing scales are determined based on the average number density
 of the sample, 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{n}$
\end_inset

, such that the smoothing scale becomes larger than 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{n}^{-1/3}$
\end_inset

.
 This is because using the smoothing scale smaller than 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{n}^{-1/3}$
\end_inset

 includes the modes which are noise-dominated.
 For fitting, we use different non-linear parameters (denoted as 
\begin_inset Formula $\Sigma$
\end_inset

